    "biography": {
      "value": "<p>A Wight-Lord is a towering undead commander — a figure of corroded mail and black iron, crowned with a circlet of dark metal. It carries a banner of frozen bone (a human spine wrapped in frozen sinew) and commands the lesser dead with terrible authority. Its eye sockets burn with pale green fire, and when it speaks, its voice is the grinding of stone on stone. Where a Wight-Lord walks, the temperature drops, breath fogs, and weapons frost over. The dead around it straighten, their shuffling replaced by purposeful, coordinated movement.</p>",
      "director": "<p>The Wight-Lord is the climactic boss of the siege encounter. It arrives at round 3-4 to give the PCs time to engage the Oath-Broken Draugr and Thralls first. Use <strong>Lord of the Barrow</strong> (+1 damage to nearby undead) to make the minions more dangerous. Open with <strong>Fellblade</strong> against the most exposed PC — the ongoing cold + frightened on tier 3 is devastating. Save <strong>Death-Gaze</strong> for ranged PCs or the healer. Use <strong>Command the Fallen</strong> (3 Malice) to summon reinforcing Thralls when the breach gets cleared. <strong>Crown of Black Iron</strong> (2 cold to adjacent creatures) punishes melee-heavy parties. When reduced to 0 HP, <strong>Undying Will</strong> triggers — the Wight-Lord survives at 1 HP with resist 5, and immediately Fellblades the nearest target. This creates a dramatic 'it won't stay down' moment. Use <strong>Grave-Command</strong> (2 Malice) to have all Thralls shift and free strike simultaneously, and <strong>Frost Roar</strong> (3 Malice) to push PCs off the wall and widen the breach.</p>",
      "languages": [
        "caelian"
      ]
    },
